Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.42,0:00:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome, one and all!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.50,0:00:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The concluding session of our\N“Pursue Peace”! Convention is about to begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.26,0:00:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,As you watch the music-video presentation,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.47,0:00:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,reflect on how learning about our Creator
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.14,0:00:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and speaking about him to others
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.43,0:00:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,can help us endure any test of faith
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.19,0:00:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,with joy and peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.23,0:00:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Please enjoy the video.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.73,0:09:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to the final portion\Nof this convention,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.95,0:09:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,which corresponds to the Sunday\Nafternoon session on your program.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.99,0:09:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The theme scripture\Nis taken from Romans 15:13,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.54,0:09:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,which says in part:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.62,0:09:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“May the God who gives hope
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.62,0:10:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,fill you with all joy and peace.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.50,0:10:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,To begin, let’s sing a song that describes
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.42,0:10:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the blessings that God’s Kingdom will bring.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.05,0:10:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The song is number 23,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.51,0:10:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,entitled “Jehovah Begins His Rule”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.72,0:10:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,—song number 23.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.77,0:13:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,In Part 1 of our feature Bible drama,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.19,0:13:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,we saw how Jehovah gave peace\Nto his servants in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.70,0:13:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,As we near the conclusion\Nof this system of things,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.32,0:13:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,how can we strengthen our confidence
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.33,0:14:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah will fulfill his promises\Nfor the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.25,0:14:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We now invite you to watch Part 2\Nof the feature Bible drama 
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.67,0:14:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{s16}{nArial}Jehovah Guides Us in the Way of Peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.40,0:14:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Bible prophecy is a fascinating subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.86,0:14:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Prophecy is far more than\Njust predictions about the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.86,0:14:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah knows all the facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.57,0:14:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He can even control and change factors
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.20,0:14:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,to ensure the outcome he desires.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.45,0:14:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,At Isaiah 55:11, he says:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.46,0:14:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“My word that goes out of my mouth . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.59,0:14:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“will not return to me without results, . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.71,0:14:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and it will have sure success.”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.63,0:14:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s prophecies
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.30,0:14:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,have a perfect record of success.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.68,0:15:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He has led his people in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.47,0:15:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So when he prophesies
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.68,0:15:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that he’ll lead his people\Nto real, lasting peace in the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.44,0:15:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,this isn’t a prediction; it’s a guarantee!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.61,0:15:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The prophecies given to Daniel
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.86,0:15:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,clearly show that God’s Kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.66,0:15:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,will without a doubt\Nbring lasting peace for all mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.06,0:15:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I have found a man from the exiles of Judah
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.93,0:15:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,who can make known the interpretation to the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.98,0:15:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I know who he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.07,0:15:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you really make known to me
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.94,0:15:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the dream that I saw
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.15,0:15:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and its interpretation?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.12,0:16:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This is your dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.09,0:16:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is the Great Timekeeper.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.21,0:16:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The prophetic portions of the book of Daniel
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.59,0:16:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,build faith by showing that Jehovah knows
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.93,0:16:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the course of history centuries
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.97,0:16:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,—even millenniums—in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.39,0:16:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,While portions of these prophecies
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.85,0:16:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,were fulfilled in Daniel’s time,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.06,0:16:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,many of the details are being fulfilled
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.06,0:16:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,right down to our day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.69,0:16:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So as we discover
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.65,0:16:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the significance of these prophecies,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.15,0:16:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re excited about what lies ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.28,0:16:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And our confidence grows as we discern
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.66,0:16:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,how Jehovah has been leading\Nhis people all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.25,0:16:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,In the days of those kings,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.71,0:16:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the God of heaven will set up a kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.50,0:16:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that will never be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.17,0:17:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The divine dream
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.22,0:17:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that Daniel interprets\Nfor King Nebuchadnezzar
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.10,0:17:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,constitutes a prophecy
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.81,0:17:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,crucial for the lasting peace of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.85,0:17:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,—a promise from Jehovah\Nto set up a Kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.82,0:17:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that would be vastly superior\Nto earthly kingdoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.03,0:17:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,History has shown us
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.16,0:17:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,how every type\Nof human government imaginable has failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.12,0:17:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So how would Jehovah’s government come?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.50,0:17:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,When would it arrive?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.29,0:17:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,These were questions\NDaniel himself likely had.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.05,0:17:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is “a Revealer of secrets.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.77,0:17:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He would eventually answer
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.85,0:17:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,these questions in due time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.39,0:17:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,As a diligent student of the Scriptures,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.23,0:17:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the prophet Daniel
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.94,0:17:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,had full faith and confidence
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.07,0:17:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in Jehovah’s ability
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.44,0:18:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to schedule events and bring them about.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.16,0:18:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And now likely in his 90’s,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.66,0:18:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel was particularly interested
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.12,0:18:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in prophecies regarding the restoration
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.96,0:18:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,of his beloved city, Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.09,0:18:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“When 70 years at Babylon are fulfilled,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.92,0:18:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will turn my attention to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.93,0:18:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“and I will make good my promise
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.97,0:18:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,by bringing you back to this place.”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.27,0:18:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremiah’s prophecy
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.31,0:18:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,had given Daniel hope
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.07,0:18:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,because it indicated that the Jews
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.82,0:18:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,would soon return to their homeland of Judah
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.07,0:18:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and rebuild Jerusalem along with its temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.03,0:18:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That makes sense\Nthat Daniel would be interested
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.16,0:18:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in the restoration of the temple\Nbecause from the time of King Solomon,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.75,0:18:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the temple in Jerusalem\Nwas the world center for worship of Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.50,0:18:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was very important to the Jews.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.13,0:19:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Scriptures,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.09,0:19:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the temple was often called\N“the house of Jehovah.”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.47,0:19:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, after Jehovah allowed young Daniel\Nand the rest of the Israelites
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.47,0:19:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to be taken captive to Babylon,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.81,0:19:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the city of Jerusalem\Nand the temple were destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.81,0:19:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So naturally, a God-fearing man like Daniel
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.73,0:19:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,would be interested\Nin seeing the temple rebuilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.78,0:19:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, as a man of faith,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.53,0:19:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel supplicates Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.62,0:19:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,O Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.79,0:19:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,do hear,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.38,0:19:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,do forgive.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.42,0:19:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,O Jehovah, do pay attention and act.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.84,0:19:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not delay,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.84,0:19:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,for your own sake,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.14,0:19:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,O my God.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.52,0:19:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,O Daniel,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.19,0:19:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,now I have come to give you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.65,0:20:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,insight and understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.36,0:20:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The visit of this angel
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.41,0:20:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,gave Daniel some answers and a hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.16,0:20:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s messenger provided
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.20,0:20:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,so many details of promises to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.54,0:20:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah assured Daniel
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.38,0:20:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that the Jews would be restored\Nto their homeland.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.50,0:20:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Their exile in Babylonia was almost over.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.55,0:20:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But that wasn’t the end\Nof the angel’s message.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.10,0:20:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He gave Daniel insight
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.31,0:20:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,into something of far greater significance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.89,0:20:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel was told when God’s people\Ncould expect the arrival
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.31,0:20:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of the foretold Messiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.77,0:20:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The Messiah would be the ruler\Nwho would make it possible
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.69,0:20:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,for obedient humans\Nto regain the blessing of perfect life
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.78,0:20:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,—free from sickness, free from death.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.91,0:20:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The Messiah would pave the way
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.12,0:20:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,for lasting peace for mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.67,0:20:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What a strengthening message
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.25,0:21:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,for Daniel to receive!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.88,0:21:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And he likely had some questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.80,0:21:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The angel told Daniel\Nthat Jerusalem and its temple
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.43,0:21:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,would be rebuilt before the Messiah arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.64,0:21:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, at the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.85,0:21:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Jerusalem and the temple were in shambles.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.89,0:21:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,How would they rebuild it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.85,0:21:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And who would be responsible for this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.40,0:21:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Babylon had been overtaken by Medo-Persia,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.48,0:21:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,pictured by the silver chest and arms
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.99,0:21:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of Nebuchadnezzar’s dream image.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.91,0:21:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Not long after
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.37,0:21:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,this change in world rulership,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.33,0:21:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Persian King Cyrus
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.62,0:21:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,issued a royal decree.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.54,0:21:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a commission from Cyrus himself
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.79,0:21:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,for the Jews to return to Jerusalem
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.80,0:21:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and rebuild the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.01,0:21:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,King Cyrus’ release of the Jews\Nwas in notable contrast
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.93,0:21:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,with the Babylonians’ desire\Nto keep them captive.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.98,0:21:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Cyrus even authorized funds
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.35,0:22:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,from the king’s house\Nto cover construction expenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.77,0:22:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would this pagan ruler
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.32,0:22:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,have any interest in, first of all,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.94,0:22:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,letting the captive Jews free and, second,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.41,0:22:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,financing the rebuilding\Nof their temple in Jerusalem?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.99,0:22:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Ezra’s words at 2 Chronicles 36:22 tell us:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.54,0:22:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah stirred the spirit\Nof King Cyrus of Persia.”
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.80,0:22:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah can maneuver events\Nto make sure his word is fulfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.68,0:22:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He can use anyone to accomplish his purpose,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.72,0:22:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and this would include\Neven a foreign king, like Cyrus.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.48,0:22:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So with this decree,\Nthe Jews returned to Judah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.20,0:22:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Launching a construction project
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.24,0:22:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and resettling an entire city
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.78,0:22:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,was a major undertaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.33,0:22:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,High Priest Jeshua and Governor Zerubbabel
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.58,0:23:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,were appointed to take the lead
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.62,0:23:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,in setting up the altar
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.21,0:23:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and rebuilding the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.13,0:23:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But this wasn’t without its challenges.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.17,0:23:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemies of Judah sought\Nto sabotage the building of the temple,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.43,0:23:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,attempting to disrupt the peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.43,0:23:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Initial attempts
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.10,0:23:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to halt the building progress failed;
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.39,0:23:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,however, eventually these enemies succeeded
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.69,0:23:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in having an official ban
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.90,0:23:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,placed on the temple-building work.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.44,0:23:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the problem here?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.03,0:23:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears the Jews let fear of man
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.82,0:23:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,stop the building work
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.03,0:23:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,after about 14 years of constant opposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.75,0:23:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, there is a bigger picture at play here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.83,0:23:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, Daniel’s prophecy foretold
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.96,0:23:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jerusalem and its temple
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.25,0:23:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,would be rebuilt before the Messiah arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.76,0:23:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, with the work halted,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.01,0:23:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the temple remained unfinished.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.80,0:23:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What would that mean\Nfor the coming of the Messiah?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.35,0:23:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeshua and Zerubbabel needed guidance.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.60,0:24:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where Jehovah\Nsteps in to provide encouragement
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.98,0:24:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,—first through the prophet Haggai.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.19,0:24:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Haggai’s clear and powerful message
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.07,0:24:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,gets right to the heart of the matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.28,0:24:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He conveys Jehovah’s direction to get up
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.03,0:24:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and keep building the temple despite opposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.87,0:24:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The Jews had a decision to make here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.79,0:24:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Would they allow opposition\Nto hinder the work?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.17,0:24:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Or would they listen to Jehovah’s words
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.63,0:24:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,through Haggai\Nand keep rebuilding the temple?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.09,0:24:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,To guide them further,\NJehovah spoke to the prophet Zechariah
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.89,0:24:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and gave him visions
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.30,0:24:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to provide the Jews with a message.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.06,0:24:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Zechariah made it clear to the Jews
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.56,0:24:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah would not allow\Ntheir opposers to harm them
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.85,0:24:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,or thwart the temple-rebuilding work.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.19,0:24:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It was only with Jehovah’s guidance\Nthat the Jews would succeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.99,0:24:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Energized by Jehovah’s motivating words\Nthrough these two prophets,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.53,0:24:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,they courageously resumed construction
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.87,0:25:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of the temple, and it was inaugurated
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.79,0:25:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in 515 B.C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.96,0:25:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it seems that at some point
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.79,0:25:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,over the following decades,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.54,0:25:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the Jews lost their initial zeal.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.96,0:25:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The temple was rebuilt and inaugurated,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.88,0:25:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jerusalem’s walls and gates remained unfinished,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.59,0:25:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,with huge gaps left in them.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.39,0:25:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That was significant because the city\Nwas surrounded by enemy nations.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.60,0:25:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the protection of these walls,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.10,0:25:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Jerusalem seemed vulnerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.40,0:25:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,When Nehemiah learned of this,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.69,0:25:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,he was visibly distressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.20,0:25:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s going on, Hanani?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.99,0:25:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How are our people?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.62,0:25:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.74,0:25:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The conditions are disgraceful.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.96,0:25:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The walls of Jerusalem are broken down,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.50,0:25:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and its gates have been burned with fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.92,0:25:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the temple?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.47,0:25:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It stands,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.43,0:25:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,but the services
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.59,0:25:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,are nothing but empty rituals.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.22,0:26:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the people and the priests
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.51,0:26:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,ignore God’s Law.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.52,0:26:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah must have been shocked
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.77,0:26:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to hear about the condition of Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.02,0:26:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,At this time, he was serving as cupbearer
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.44,0:26:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Persian King in Shushan.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.53,0:26:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The journey from Shushan to Jerusalem
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.99,0:26:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,was about 1,000 miles (1,600 km).
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.03,0:26:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Still,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.99,0:26:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah felt compelled to act.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.21,0:26:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah rejoiced at the prospect
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.13,0:26:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of rebuilding the walls.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.09,0:26:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The Jews at this time
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.09,0:26:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,were still fearful of their opposers,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.18,0:26:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,but Nehemiah was intent on changing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.77,0:26:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew that Jehovah was behind the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.65,0:26:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And if Jehovah is behind something,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.98,0:26:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,there’s no amount of opposition\Nthat can thwart his will,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.69,0:26:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,so the wall repairs began.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.28,0:27:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn’t to say
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.70,0:27:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that there were not challenges along the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.58,0:27:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Opposers did not give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.50,0:27:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I recommend we turn the accusation
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.25,0:27:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of sedition against Nehemiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.59,0:27:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s brilliant!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.59,0:27:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.80,0:27:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,he will beg for our help.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.10,0:27:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,These opposers threatened the Jews,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.56,0:27:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,schemed against them,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.31,0:27:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and even accused Nehemiah of treason.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.77,0:27:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah’s peace and the peace
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.86,0:27:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Jews supporting the work was threatened.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.61,0:27:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But despite the attempts of opposers,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.08,0:27:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah and the Jews looked to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.70,0:27:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,for guidance and kept working.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.92,0:27:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,When Jehovah declares his purpose,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.55,0:27:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,there is nothing that can prevent him
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.67,0:27:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,from carrying it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.72,0:28:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So if Jehovah wanted a rebuilt Jerusalem,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.51,0:28:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,complete with rebuilt walls,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.06,0:28:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah would have\Ncomplete faith in Jehovah’s ability
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.10,0:28:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to support the rebuilding efforts.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.48,0:28:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And with this support,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.52,0:28:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the city walls were completed
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.24,0:28:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,in just 52 days.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.91,0:28:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah, the wall is complete!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.29,0:28:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.79,0:28:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,With rebuilt walls and a rebuilt temple,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.96,0:28:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,physically the city was in good condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.21,0:28:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,However, about 12 years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.51,0:28:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah returned to Shushan.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.80,0:28:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,During his prolonged absence,\Nthe spiritual state of the Jews deteriorated.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.31,0:28:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It was so sad,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.89,0:28:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,as many in Israel\Nfell back into bad practices.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.98,0:28:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Some in the priesthood,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.48,0:28:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,including High Priest Eliashib,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.32,0:29:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,no longer took their responsibilities seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.66,0:29:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, Jehovah raised up the prophet Malachi 
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.16,0:29:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to counsel the negligent priests.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.16,0:29:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Why have you Levites despised Jehovah’s name?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.71,0:29:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Despised it?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.83,0:29:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You present a blind,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.42,0:29:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,lame, or sick animal as a sacrifice
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.67,0:29:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and say that it is nothing bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.71,0:29:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Should Jehovah accept it from your hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.47,0:29:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And there’s another thing you do
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.22,0:29:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,so that he no longer
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.80,0:29:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,looks favorably on anything you offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.39,0:29:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you betray the wife of your youth,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.64,0:29:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,although she’s your partner, your legal wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.56,0:29:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The lips of a priest
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.60,0:29:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,should safeguard knowledge,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.36,0:29:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and people should seek the law from his mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.15,0:29:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But you,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.03,0:29:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you have made many stumble.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.66,0:29:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Evidently, Malachi’s words
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.24,0:29:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,had little effect on the priesthood.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.45,0:29:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite his warnings,\Nthe people refused to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.00,0:29:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,When Nehemiah returned,\Nwhat he found shocked him.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.25,0:30:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,For a long time,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.34,0:30:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the priests and the Levites
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.67,0:30:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,have not taken their duties seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.47,0:30:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,When the people saw that,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.89,0:30:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,they stopped bringing in tithes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.51,0:30:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the tithes,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.85,0:30:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,most Levites and singers
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.77,0:30:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,returned to their fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.14,0:30:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Eliashib
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.31,0:30:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,not tell the people to bring your provisions?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.23,0:30:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,In your absence,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.65,0:30:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the prophet Malachi warned him
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.19,0:30:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the priests.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.94,0:30:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But Eliashib—
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.95,0:30:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He took our storeroom
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.66,0:30:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and emptied it of our provisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.45,0:30:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He gave it to Tobiah to use as a dining hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.45,0:30:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.08,0:30:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to no longer providing\Nfinancial support,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.17,0:30:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the people started\Nconducting business on the Sabbath.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.80,0:30:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you selling today?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.84,0:30:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Only the best quality fish from Tyre.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.30,0:30:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They were marrying foreign women.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.80,0:30:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m marrying Gizla today.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.39,0:30:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Gizla?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.60,0:30:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That Moabite girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.35,0:30:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard you bind yourself with an oath
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.48,0:30:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and a curse not to take a wife from the nations!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.48,0:31:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This action could have disrupted
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.44,0:31:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the line to the Messiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.82,0:31:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and it definitely threatened\Nto contaminate pure worship.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.66,0:31:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,These men were bringing the restored nation
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.83,0:31:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,into disfavor with Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.41,0:31:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the same reason\Nwhy Jehovah allowed Babylon
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.75,0:31:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to destroy Jerusalem in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.50,0:31:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So Nehemiah took action\Nagainst these faithless ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.93,0:31:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Please cleanse this room
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.39,0:31:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and replace the utensils.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.48,0:31:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.93,0:31:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.56,0:31:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And gather all the Levites,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.81,0:31:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the singers, and the deputy rulers to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.85,0:31:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m assigning them all back to their posts.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.77,0:31:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He enforced the strict observance
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.61,0:31:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Sabbath. 
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.49,0:31:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.74,0:31:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to sleep on the ground last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.86,0:31:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You know God’s Law:
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.28,0:31:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,No work,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.20,0:31:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,no business on the Sabbath!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.29,0:31:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.16,0:31:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You and all the Levites, guard the gates
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.37,0:31:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and keep the Sabbath holy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.96,0:31:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t let anyone in!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.34,0:32:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He disciplined those\Nwho had taken foreign wives.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.47,0:32:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you not swear never to marry someone
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.34,0:32:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,who doesn’t serve Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.64,0:32:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Nehemiah, nobody cares.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.64,0:32:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.31,0:32:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.39,0:32:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Then why have you ignored the command of Jehovah 
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.85,0:32:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and your own oath?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.52,0:32:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s no doubt
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.36,0:32:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah\Nwas guiding Nehemiah’s efforts all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.36,0:32:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,After a spiritual cleansing was done,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.82,0:32:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,a measure of peace was again enjoyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.33,0:32:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And with this vigorous
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.70,0:32:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,rooting out of apostasy,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.37,0:32:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the record of the Hebrew Scriptures
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.88,0:32:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,comes to a close.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.05,0:32:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we don’t have\Nan inspired record of events
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.63,0:32:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in the centuries leading up to Jesus’ birth,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.59,0:32:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,but history shows that Jerusalem
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.72,0:32:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,underwent several changes during these years.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.35,0:32:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The Medo-Persian Empire
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.77,0:32:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,was overtaken by Greece,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.40,0:33:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,represented by the copper belly and thighs
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.77,0:33:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of Nebuchadnezzar’s dream image.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.23,0:33:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,While the city seemed to survive\Nthe change in control
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.61,0:33:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,without any physical damage,\Nits spiritual state was threatened.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.32,0:33:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The Greek Empire set the stage for the spread
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.37,0:33:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,of Greek language, culture, and religious thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.67,0:33:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and Israel was affected by this influence.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.79,0:33:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Years later, King Antiochus IV
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.30,0:33:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,was determined to eradicate\NJewish worship and customs.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.97,0:33:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He went so far as to sacrifice a pig
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.39,0:33:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Greek god Zeus
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.51,0:33:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,at the temple of Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.14,0:33:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This was a vicious attempt
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.14,0:33:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to defile and to stamp out pure worship.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.90,0:33:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the desecration\Nhad the opposite effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.07,0:33:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It sparked an uprising
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.15,0:33:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of zealous Jews, and three years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.74,0:33:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,they cleansed the temple
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.11,0:33:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and rededicated it to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.74,0:33:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,About a century later,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.74,0:33:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Jerusalem experienced\Nanother change in rulership
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.75,0:34:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,as Rome became the dominant world power.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.84,0:34:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Rome corresponded to the legs of iron
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.42,0:34:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,in Nebuchadnezzar’s dream image.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.51,0:34:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Under the rule
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.93,0:34:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,of Herod the Great,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.26,0:34:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Jerusalem enjoyed considerable prosperity.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.10,0:34:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Herod’s greatest work, however,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.22,0:34:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,was the reconstruction of the temple
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.43,0:34:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and its building complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.23,0:34:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The temple and its daily sacrifices
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.27,0:34:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,remained in operation down to Jesus’ day.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.94,0:34:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible record picks up
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.82,0:34:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,before Jesus was born.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.96,0:34:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,May Jehovah have mercy on us!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.71,0:34:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.26,0:34:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the sun up already?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.55,0:34:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.13,0:34:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,are they . . . angels?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.88,0:34:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not be afraid,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.39,0:34:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,for look!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.14,0:34:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I am declaring to you good news
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.97,0:35:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of a great joy that all the people will have.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.52,0:35:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,For today there was born
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.52,0:35:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to you in David’s city a savior, 
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.02,0:35:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,who is Christ the Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.15,0:35:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus’ birth and ministry
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.19,0:35:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,fulfilled many prophecies.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.24,0:35:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In 29 C.E., Jehovah\Nanointed Jesus with holy spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.78,0:35:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This corresponds exactly\Nto the words of Daniel’s prophecy
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.83,0:35:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah gave him\Nmore than 500 years earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.92,0:35:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The promised Messiah had arrived!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.88,0:35:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Early in his ministry, Jesus read these words
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.59,0:35:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,from the prophecy of Isaiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.26,0:35:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The scroll of Isaiah the prophet reads:
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.76,0:35:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah’s spirit is upon me,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.43,0:35:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“because he anointed me
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.73,0:35:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“to declare good news to the poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.40,0:35:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“He sent me
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.11,0:35:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“to proclaim liberty to the captives 
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.86,0:35:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“and a recovery of sight to the blind,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.40,0:35:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“to send the crushed ones away free,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.20,0:35:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to preach Jehovah’s acceptable year.”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.92,0:36:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Today this scripture
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.42,0:36:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that you just heard is fulfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.64,0:36:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Holy spirit empowered Jesus to perform
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.93,0:36:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,many miracles\Nin just a few short years on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.60,0:36:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This had a profound effect\Non the people living in his day.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.32,0:36:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I am a very sick woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.53,0:36:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve suffered from a flow of blood
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.78,0:36:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,for some 12 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.57,0:36:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,He can heal me!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.83,0:36:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if I could touch
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.00,0:36:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,just the fringes
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.04,0:36:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,of his outer garment, I will get well!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.26,0:37:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Who touched my outer garment?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.26,0:37:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Who touched me?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.35,0:37:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.44,0:37:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,please forgive me, my Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.73,0:37:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It was I who touched you!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.11,0:37:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I have faith in you!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.11,0:37:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that if I could just touch
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.57,0:37:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the fringes of your outer garment,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.07,0:37:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I could get well.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.62,0:37:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Take courage, daughter!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.66,0:37:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Your faith has made you well.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.21,0:37:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The miracles Jesus performed were unlike
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.80,0:37:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,anything the people had seen before.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.88,0:37:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, the people had hope
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.89,0:37:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,—a hope for the future, a hope for peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.81,0:37:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,He even demonstrated that he had power\Nfar beyond any human ruler.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.19,0:37:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord, Mary is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.45,0:38:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.87,0:38:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,If you had been here,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.91,0:38:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,my brother would not have died!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.13,0:38:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Lazarus!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.51,0:38:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Come out!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.40,0:38:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Free him, and let him go!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.03,0:38:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There is so much we can learn
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.28,0:38:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,from Jesus’ miracles, works, and teachings.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.66,0:38:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They reveal Jehovah’s purpose and power.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.91,0:38:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They show how enjoyable,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.75,0:38:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,how peaceful life will be\Nunder God’s Messianic Ruler.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.71,0:38:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Humans alive at this time\Ncould see visible proof of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.63,0:39:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus’ ministry accomplished so much
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.60,0:39:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in just three and a half years.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.35,0:39:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And prophecy regarding the Messiah
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.77,0:39:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,continued to be fulfilled\Nas his opposers succeeded
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.44,0:39:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in putting him to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.41,0:39:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,With the sacrifice
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.04,0:39:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of Jesus’ perfect human life,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.71,0:39:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the entire arrangement
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.67,0:39:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,for worshipping Jehovah had changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.63,0:39:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no longer a need\Nfor animal sacrifices.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.55,0:39:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Pure worship was no longer centered\Naround the temple in Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.18,0:39:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The only way to worship Jehovah acceptably\Nwas through the Messiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.18,0:39:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Now people everywhere\Ncould find the way to peace
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.89,0:39:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,through faith in Jesus’ ransom sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.36,0:39:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The Jewish system of worship
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.36,0:39:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,under the Mosaic Law was over.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.40,0:40:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Jerusalem and the temple\Nno longer had Jehovah’s favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.86,0:40:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus’ perfect human sacrifice
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.49,0:40:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,was the only solution for lasting peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.58,0:40:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what did this mean\Nfor the city of Jerusalem and the temple?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.58,0:40:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, before his death,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.58,0:40:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus provided his followers with a warning
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.30,0:40:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,regarding Jerusalem’s destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.55,0:40:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,At Luke 21:20, 21, he says:
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.18,0:40:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“When you see Jerusalem
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.18,0:40:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“surrounded by encamped armies,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.47,0:40:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“then know that the desolating of her
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.52,0:40:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“has drawn near. . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.85,0:40:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“Let those in the midst of her leave,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.48,0:40:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and let those in the countryside\Nnot enter into her.”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.15,0:40:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,A good ruler guides his people.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.94,0:40:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Although it wasn’t yet time for him\Nto take the throne as Ruler of God’s Kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.24,0:40:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus (by the way he acted) gave us insight\Ninto the kind of ruler he would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.41,0:40:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,By providing first-century Christians
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.54,0:40:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,with a warning to leave Jerusalem
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.63,0:40:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and all Judea,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.00,0:41:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,he was guiding them and protecting them.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.13,0:41:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus prophesied the destruction of the city,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.01,0:41:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and just a few decades later,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.09,0:41:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that prophecy came true.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.14,0:41:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The Roman Empire still had control of Judea,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.68,0:41:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and tensions ran high
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.27,0:41:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,between the Romans and the Jews.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.52,0:41:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, the Jews
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.15,0:41:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,revolted against Roman rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.12,0:41:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,With the city surrounded
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.12,0:41:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and Roman forces closing in,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.83,0:41:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,it seemed there was no way out.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.83,0:41:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah’s word cannot go unfulfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.88,0:41:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,For no apparent reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.21,0:41:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the Roman forces withdrew!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.39,0:41:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,For faithful Christians,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.39,0:41:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,this was their opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.64,0:41:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s simple:
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.65,0:41:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who followed Jesus’ direction
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.69,0:42:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to leave Judea were guided to safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.36,0:42:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,For those who delayed,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.36,0:42:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,escape became difficult or impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.08,0:42:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no doubt
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.16,0:42:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jerusalem no longer enjoyed\NJehovah’s special favor and protection.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.18,0:42:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The city and its temple
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.18,0:42:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,were completely destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.15,0:42:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,There are parallels we can draw\Nfrom the warning Jesus gave
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.69,0:42:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to those first-century Christians
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.16,0:42:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to the warning we\Nhave been given for our day.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.91,0:42:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus gave us one composite sign
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.74,0:42:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that indicates the destruction\Nof this current system of things
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.08,0:42:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is very close.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.12,0:43:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Prophecies in the Bible give us no doubt
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.67,0:43:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that we are living in “the last days.”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.92,0:43:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has not revealed all the details\Nof how everything will work out.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.26,0:43:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But we know that everything\Nhe has revealed will come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.39,0:43:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This includes details outlining\Nhow world events
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.68,0:43:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,would unfold in the time\Nof the end
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.89,0:43:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,before mankind\Nwould experience permanent peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.65,0:43:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, Daniel’s prophecy indicated
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.32,0:43:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that there would be\Nonly one dominant world power in place
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.03,0:43:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,at the time of the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.66,0:43:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,By World War I,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.20,0:43:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the power represented by the feet 
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.04,0:43:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,of iron and clay had emerged.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.41,0:43:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,During that war, Britain and America
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.67,0:43:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,forged a partnership
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.63,0:43:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that continued through the Second World War.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.05,0:43:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This means a special relationship
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.30,0:43:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,between the British Commonwealth and Empire
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.39,0:43:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and the United States of America.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.93,0:43:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither the sure prevention of war
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.94,0:44:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,nor the continuous rise
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.94,0:44:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of world organization will begin
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.94,0:44:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,without what I have called
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.99,0:44:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the fraternal association
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.28,0:44:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,of the English-speaking people.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.66,0:44:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,These two countries
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.71,0:44:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,continue to be a dual\NEnglish-speaking world power.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.42,0:44:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The characteristics of iron and clay
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.71,0:44:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,used to represent\Nthis world power are significant.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.84,0:44:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And as the toes of the feet
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.84,0:44:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,were partly of iron and partly of clay,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.64,0:44:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,so the kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.64,0:44:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,will be partly strong and partly fragile.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.15,0:44:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,At times, the United States and Britain
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.52,0:44:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,have displayed ironlike strength
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.65,0:44:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,through their involvement in armed conflicts.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.57,0:44:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,However, iron mixed with clay\Nis considerably weakened.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.49,0:44:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,This can be observed as common people
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.04,0:45:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,undermined the Anglo-American\NWorld Power’s ability
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.29,0:45:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to act with ironlike strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.88,0:45:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,As the political and social developments
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.88,0:45:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,foretold in the Bible come to a climax,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.68,0:45:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,we have a measure of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.84,0:45:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We know Jehovah will guide his people,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.51,0:45:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,even as the world’s spiritual\Nand moral condition sinks to new depths.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.31,0:45:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,As many in first-century Jerusalem
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.44,0:45:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,continued their lives
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.48,0:45:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,as if nothing had changed,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.61,0:45:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,so, too, today many
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.74,0:45:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,continue on with their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.86,0:45:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, we remain alert
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.87,0:45:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,as we see fulfillment of Bible prophecy
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.58,0:45:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,right before our eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.04,0:45:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,In the days of those kings,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.83,0:45:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the God of heaven will set up a kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.50,0:45:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that will never be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.46,0:45:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The book of Revelation
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.47,0:45:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,tells us what will soon happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.68,0:45:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The political rulers of the world\Nwill give the United Nations
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.60,0:46:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,unprecedented power and authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.68,0:46:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The apostle Paul foretold\Nthat the nations will declare
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.48,0:46:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,“Peace and security!”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.15,0:46:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But it won’t prove to be true peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.53,0:46:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The nations supporting the UN
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.24,0:46:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,will attack the institutions\Nof false religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.08,0:46:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Then a coalition of earth’s governments\Nthat the prophet Ezekiel
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.96,0:46:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,calls “Gog of the land of Magog”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.21,0:46:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,will attack God’s people.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.59,0:46:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, we don’t need to be fearful.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.35,0:46:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s when we can put into action
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.76,0:46:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,all of the lessons we’ve learned.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.64,0:46:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who trust and obey Jehovah’s guidance
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.35,0:46:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,can look to the near future with confidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.90,0:46:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,As we’ve seen, Jehovah has always been
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.90,0:46:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in control of the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.90,0:46:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He has never guided his people
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.90,0:46:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in a certain direction\Nbut then failed to provide for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.24,0:47:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s why we can say\Nthat the lessons we learn
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.41,0:47:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,from the faithful men we’ve studied
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.41,0:47:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,are more than just lessons.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.42,0:47:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This has been Jehovah\Npaving the way for peace from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.25,0:47:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking back, we see exactly\Nhow Jehovah has led his people.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.92,0:47:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It took many years,\Nbut he’s been in control the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.14,0:47:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Would it make sense\Nto think he isn’t in control anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.89,0:47:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,No power in heaven or on earth
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.89,0:47:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,can prevent Jehovah\Nfrom accomplishing his express purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.86,0:47:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He has never relinquished control,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.69,0:47:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and he is still guiding his people.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.82,0:47:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now think about this:
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.86,0:47:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If Jehovah has guided\Nhis people to this point,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.08,0:47:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,we can have full confidence
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.12,0:47:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that trust and obedience to his direction
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.21,0:47:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,will prove to be our salvation,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.96,0:47:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,even if a way out seems impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.21,0:47:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is all-powerful!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.72,0:48:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s going to help us\Nthrough whatever we may face.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.60,0:48:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We won’t have to fight,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.36,0:48:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and we won’t need to fear annihilation.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.32,0:48:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has things
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.24,0:48:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,under control.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.37,0:48:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“And this kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.00,0:48:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“will not be passed on to any other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.92,0:48:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“It will crush and put an end
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.96,0:48:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“to all these kingdoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.61,0:48:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And it alone will stand forever.”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.36,0:48:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,God’s Kingdom will fill
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.36,0:48:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and renew the entire earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.37,0:49:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s promises
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.37,0:49:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,will be completely fulfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.96,0:49:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Lasting peace will finally become
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.04,0:49:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,a reality for all mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.05,0:49:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Just imagine what faithful servants
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.17,0:49:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,have to look forward to\Nunder Jesus’ heavenly rule!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.43,0:49:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He will be able to provide\Nwhat no man ever could.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.43,0:49:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine what that will be like?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.08,0:49:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“For look!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.50,0:49:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“I am creating new heavens and a new earth;
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.71,0:49:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the former things\Nwill not be called to mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.93,0:50:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,nor will they come up into the heart.”
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.56,0:50:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“The righteous will possess the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.19,0:50:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and they will live forever on it.”
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.25,0:50:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“He will swallow up death forever,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.13,0:50:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Sovereign Lord Jehovah\Nwill wipe away the tears from all faces.”
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.98,0:50:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“He will wipe out every tear from their eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.94,0:51:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“and death will be no more, 
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.95,0:51:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“neither will mourning
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.03,0:51:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“nor outcry nor pain be anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.58,0:51:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The former things have passed away.”
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.40,0:51:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“At that time the eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.82,0:51:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“of the blind will be opened,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.03,0:51:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the ears of the deaf will be unstopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.67,0:51:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“At that time the lame
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.08,0:51:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,“will leap like the deer,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.71,0:52:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the tongue of the speechless
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.80,0:52:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“will shout for joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.10,0:52:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“For waters will burst forth\Nin the wilderness,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.19,0:52:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and streams in the desert plain.”
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.32,0:52:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“They will build houses and live in them,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.88,0:52:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and they will plant vineyards\Nand eat their fruitage.”
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.48,0:52:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“For the days of my people\Nwill be like the days of a tree,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.52,0:52:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the work of their hands
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.11,0:53:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,my chosen ones will enjoy to the full.”
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.49,0:53:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“But the meek will possess the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.29,0:53:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“and they will find exquisite delight
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.92,0:53:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in the abundance of peace.”
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.60,0:53:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What a faith-strengthening drama!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.44,0:53:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We are at peace knowing that Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.61,0:53:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is in complete control.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.57,0:53:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All in attendance will be pleased to know\Nthat Parts 1 and 2
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.11,0:53:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,of the drama-documentary\N{\i1}{s16}{nArial}Jehovah Guides Us in the Way of Peace
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.66,0:53:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,are available now for download on jw.org
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.38,0:54:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you enjoyed the original songs
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.38,0:54:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that have been featured\Nat recent conventions?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.22,0:54:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We now have the privilege\Nof watching a video medley
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.43,0:54:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and reflecting on the lessons we have learned
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.81,0:54:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,at our conventions over the past few years.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.10,0:54:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Enjoy!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.29,0:54:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Doubt and fear surround me—
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.63,0:54:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The way ahead not clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.51,0:54:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Through uncertainty you guide me;
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.68,0:54:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you’re always near.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.06,0:54:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Life may not be easy,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.56,0:55:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But this I know is true:
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.69,0:55:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re the God who’s ever loyal;
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.82,0:55:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,My life is safe with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.91,0:55:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, give me eyes of faith
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.25,0:55:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And help me always see
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.88,0:55:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,There are more with us than against us.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.97,0:55:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Courageous let me be.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.56,0:55:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Courage, give me courage;
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.85,0:55:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,With courage, I’ll endure.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.27,0:55:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, give me courage;
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.32,0:55:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Your victory is sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.58,0:56:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Feeling fear is human.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.96,0:56:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In my own strength, I’m frail.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.96,0:56:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You have been my rock and refuge;
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.09,0:56:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Your power never fails.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.43,0:56:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Help me be courageous,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.23,0:56:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And let my heart be brave.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.98,0:56:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Lasting harm can never hold me—
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.16,0:56:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,No prison, gate, or grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.33,0:56:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, give me eyes of faith
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.63,0:56:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And help me always see
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.30,0:56:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There are more with us than against us.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.26,0:56:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Courageous let me be.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.97,0:57:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Courage, give me courage;
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.40,0:57:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,With courage, I’ll endure.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.53,0:57:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, give me courage;
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.16,0:57:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Your victory is sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.13,0:57:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Look around us now;
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.97,0:57:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,See the love on each face—
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.85,0:57:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Out there in the world, hard to find.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.60,0:57:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,All these faithful friends
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.86,0:57:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,With the love they all show,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.57,0:57:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Glad to leave that old world behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.62,0:58:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Love never fails; that’s promised.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.59,0:58:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It always will endure.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.05,0:58:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Love—unfailing love—
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.18,0:58:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what Jehovah gives.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.89,0:58:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.77,0:58:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Love—unfailing love—
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.07,0:58:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what we need to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.74,0:58:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And the love here today,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.24,0:58:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In our heart may it stay—
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.17,0:58:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Love—unfailing love—
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.38,0:58:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what Jehovah gives.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.18,0:59:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.77,0:59:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Love—unfailing love—
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.90,0:59:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what we need to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.65,0:59:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And the love here today,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.28,0:59:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,In our heart may it stay—
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.95,0:59:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfailing love,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.88,0:59:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfailing love,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.76,0:59:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfailing love.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.85,0:59:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should I fear the lion?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.61,0:59:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should I fear any foe?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.66,1:00:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,With Jehovah by my side,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.58,1:00:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I will not run and hide.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.04,1:00:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,My God is with me; this I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.96,1:00:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,With eyes of faith,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.71,1:00:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I see beyond the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.84,1:00:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,With eyes of faith,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.51,1:00:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,there’s nothing more to fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.06,1:00:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,With Jehovah, I am strong,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.06,1:00:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Determined to go on,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.82,1:00:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Knowing that my God is always near—
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.53,1:00:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,With eyes of faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.50,1:01:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I see the wondrous future
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.30,1:01:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,God has in store for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.60,1:01:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to be strong.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.15,1:01:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it won’t be long
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.19,1:01:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Till Jehovah claims his victory.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.53,1:01:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,With eyes of faith,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.37,1:01:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I see beyond the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.50,1:01:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,With eyes of faith,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.17,1:01:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,there’s nothing more to fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.55,1:01:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,With Jehovah, I am strong,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.63,1:01:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Determined to go on,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.51,1:01:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Knowing that my God is always near—
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.65,1:01:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,With eyes of faith,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.41,1:02:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,With eyes of faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.59,1:02:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The stars that fill the summer night
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.80,1:02:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Look down from above.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.22,1:02:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The beauty of the day and night
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.77,1:02:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You fashioned with love.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.11,1:02:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Your hands prepared the land and sea,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.61,1:02:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And ev’rything that came to be
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.99,1:02:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Brought joy to your heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.91,1:02:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,There is joy in your creation,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.17,1:02:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,In the message of salvation,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.50,1:03:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Paradise to come.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.47,1:03:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But to have your love forever
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.80,1:03:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Is a real and lasting treasure.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.39,1:03:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You alone will prove to be
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.31,1:03:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Our joy eternally.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.75,1:03:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This joy could not be ours
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.46,1:03:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the gift of your Son.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.50,1:03:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,His sacrifice has paid the price
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.09,1:03:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So joy could be ours for all time.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.68,1:03:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There is joy in your creation,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.23,1:03:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In the message of salvation,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.69,1:04:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Paradise to come.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.44,1:04:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But to have your love forever
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.91,1:04:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Is a real and lasting treasure.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.49,1:04:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You alone will prove to be
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.54,1:04:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Our joy eternally.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.14,1:04:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Our next song encourages us
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.85,1:04:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to look ahead with confidence.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.35,1:04:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The song is entitled\N“See Yourself When All Is New.”
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.36,1:04:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s sing together song number 139.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.61,1:04:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s song number 139.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.42,0:00:24.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さん ようこそ！
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.71,0:00:29.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,「平和をつくる」地区大会\N3日目午後の部です
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.59,0:00:32.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,これから ミュージックビデオを\Nご覧ください
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.76,0:00:37.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,創造者エホバについて学び\N人々に伝えることは
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.52,0:00:43.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,喜びや平和を失わずに\N信仰の試練を忍耐する助けになります
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.36,0:00:45.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうぞお楽しみください
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.94,0:09:44.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,大会3日目午後の部に
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.98,0:09:49.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんを改めて歓迎いたします
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.32,0:09:55.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,3日目の主題は\Nローマ 15:13から取られています
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.37,0:09:57.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,「希望を与える神が ⋯⋯皆さんを
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.91,0:10:01.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,あらゆる喜びと平和で\N満たしてくださ［る］」
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.75,0:10:07.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 神の王国がもたらす祝福を\N描いた歌を歌いましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.13,0:10:12.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,23番です 主題は\N「エホバは統治を始める」です
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.93,0:10:15.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,歌は23番です
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.89,0:13:48.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,ドラマの第1部では\Nエホバが昔の人たちに
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.73,0:13:52.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのように平和を与えたかを\N見ることができました
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.02,0:13:56.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,終わりが近い今 私たちは
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.24,0:14:01.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが将来に関するご自分の約束を\N果たしてくださる という確信を
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.49,0:14:04.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのように強められるでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.87,0:14:09.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 「エホバは平和へと\N導いてくださる」というドラマの
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.96,0:14:12.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,第2部をお楽しみください
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.47,0:14:30.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の預言は本当に素晴らしいです
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.27,0:14:34.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,単に将来のことを前もって\N言っているだけではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.90,0:14:37.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは全てを知っています
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.74,0:14:42.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 思い描いた通りに\N事を導くこともできます
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.32,0:14:45.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,イザヤ 55:11でこう言っています
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.87,0:14:48.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私の口から出る言葉［は］
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.00,0:14:51.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,成果を収めずに\N私のもとに戻ることはない
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.46,0:14:55.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,必ず私の望むことを成し遂げ［る］」
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.84,0:14:59.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの預言は\N100パーセント実現してきました
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.72,0:15:02.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,その通りになるよう\Nエホバは導いてきました
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.80,0:15:06.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで 私たちを平和へと導くという
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.18,0:15:09.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの預言も必ずその通りになります
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.68,0:15:13.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,間違いありません 絶対にそうなります
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.52,0:15:16.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル書に書かれている\N預言を調べると
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.57,0:15:22.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の王国によって全人類が\N平和になるということを確信できます
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.64,0:15:48.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,ユダで捕らえた人の中で\N王の夢を解き明かせる者を見つけました
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.39,0:15:51.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰かは分かっている
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.43,0:15:57.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,おまえは本当に私が見た夢の内容を話し\N解き明かせるのか
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.91,0:16:09.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,これが あなたが見た夢です
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.12,0:16:15.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは自分が決めた\Nタイミングを必ず守ります
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.75,0:16:20.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル書の預言を学ぶと\Nエホバへの信仰が強まります
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.21,0:16:25.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは将来のことを何百年\Nいや 何千年も前から知っています
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.34,0:16:28.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,預言の一部はダニエルの時代に\Nその通りになりましたが
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.85,0:16:34.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,大部分はその後 今に至るまでの間に\N実現してきています
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.35,0:16:37.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,この大切な預言の意味を知ると
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.69,0:16:40.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,将来に大きな期待が持てます
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.07,0:16:44.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに導かれた人たちのことを\N考えると エホバへの信頼は
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.36,0:16:46.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,ますます強まります
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.91,0:16:49.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,この王たちの時代に
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.95,0:16:54.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,天の神は決して滅ぼされることのない\N王国を建てます
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.79,0:17:03.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルがネブカドネザル王に\N解き明かした神からの夢は
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.38,0:17:10.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,神が人類をどのように平和にするかを\N知る上で とても重要な預言です
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.60,0:17:15.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,その預言によれば エホバは\N地球上のどんな国よりも
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.19,0:17:18.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,はるかに優れた王国を設立します
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.02,0:17:23.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,歴史を通じて これまで\Nいろいろなタイプの政府がありましたが
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.82,0:17:26.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,どれもうまくいきませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.53,0:17:30.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,では どのようにして\N王国が建てられるのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.83,0:17:33.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,それはいつのことでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.62,0:17:38.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,恐らく ダニエルも\Nそう疑問に思ったはずです
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.80,0:17:47.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは秘密を明らかにする神です
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.26,0:17:51.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,時が来れば\N疑問に答えてくれるはずです
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.72,0:17:55.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルは聖書を学ぶことを\N習慣にしていたので
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.52,0:18:01.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは予定したことを必ず実行する\Nということを確信していました
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.19,0:18:04.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 恐らく\N90代になってからのことです
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.90,0:18:11.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルは 愛する都市エルサレムの\N復興についての預言に関心を持ちます
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.70,0:18:18.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,「バビロンで70年が満了したら
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.83,0:18:22.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,私はあなたたちに注意を向ける
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.21,0:18:26.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,私の約束を果たし
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.59,0:18:31.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたたちをこの場所に連れ戻す」
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.18,0:18:36.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,エレミヤの預言を読んで\N希望を持てたはずです
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.81,0:18:39.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,ユダヤ人が間もなく故郷のユダに戻って
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.90,0:18:43.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムと神殿を建て直す\Nということが分かったからです
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.02,0:18:48.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルが神殿の再建に\N関心を持ったのは 自然なことでした
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.36,0:18:51.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,ソロモン王の時代から\Nエルサレムの神殿は
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.62,0:18:54.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの崇拝の中心地だったからです
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.45,0:18:58.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,ユダヤ人みんなにとって\Nとても重要な場所でした
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.08,0:19:04.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の中で 神殿はしばしば\N「エホバの家」と呼ばれています
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.29,0:19:07.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,ところが 若者だったダニエルが
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.13,0:19:11.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほかのイスラエル人たちと一緒に\Nバビロンに連れていかれた後
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.80,0:19:15.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムの都市と神殿は\N破壊されてしまいました
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.02,0:19:20.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで ダニエルのように\N神に心から仕える人は
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.06,0:19:24.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,神殿が再建されるのを見たいと\N思ったはずです
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.44,0:19:29.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰のあついダニエルは\N再びエホバに祈ります
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.78,0:19:35.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバ 聞いてください
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.08,0:19:38.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,お許しください
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.70,0:19:41.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちに注意を向けて
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.58,0:19:44.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,救ってください！
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.25,0:19:47.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたご自身のために
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.13,0:19:50.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,行動を遅らせないでください
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.39,0:19:56.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.77,0:20:02.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,私はあなたに洞察と理解を\N与えるために来ました
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.48,0:20:08.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,やって来た天使がダニエルの祈りに答え
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.65,0:20:11.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,希望を持てるようにしました
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.15,0:20:16.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは天使を通して\Nこの先どうなるのかを詳しく伝えました
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.41,0:20:21.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,ユダヤ人は必ず故国に戻ることができる\Nと言って 安心させました
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.66,0:20:25.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,バビロンでの捕囚の生活は\Nもうすぐ終わります
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.84,0:20:29.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 天使が伝えたのは\Nそれだけではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.30,0:20:34.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,それよりももっとスケールの大きな事に\Nついてダニエルに教えました
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.43,0:20:39.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルは 約束されていたメシアが\Nいつ現れるかについて聞きました
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.77,0:20:44.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,メシアが王になり\N人類は神が最初に考えていた通り
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.40,0:20:46.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつまでも生きられるようになります
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.77,0:20:49.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,病気はなくなり 死ぬこともありません
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.03,0:20:55.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,メシアが人類の\N平和のための道をつくります
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.16,0:21:01.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,それを聞いて ダニエルは\Nどんなにうれしかったことでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.12,0:21:03.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,きっといろんな疑問が\N湧いてきたはずです
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.83,0:21:07.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,天使はダニエルに エルサレムと神殿は
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.34,0:21:10.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,メシアが現れる前に\N再建される と言いました
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.88,0:21:15.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも その頃 エルサレムと神殿は\N廃墟と化していました
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.97,0:21:20.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,いったい誰が どのようにして\N建て直すのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.43,0:21:23.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,バビロンはやがて\Nメディア・ペルシャに征服されます
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.89,0:21:29.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネブカドネザルが見た像の\N銀の胸と腕に相当する国です
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.32,0:21:36.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,征服して間もなく\Nペルシャのキュロス王は布告を出します
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.24,0:21:39.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,それはユダヤ人への王直々の命令で
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.74,0:21:44.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムに戻って神殿を\N建て直すようにというものでした
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.71,0:21:50.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,このキュロスの対応は
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.71,0:21:56.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,ユダヤ人を何十年も捕囚にしていた\Nバビロンとは大きく違うものでした
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.30,0:22:01.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,キュロスは自分の財宝を使って\N建設費用を賄う とさえ言いました
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.72,0:22:04.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,異教の神を崇拝する王が
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.23,0:22:09.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,いったいどうして捕囚のユダヤ人を\N解放しようと思うのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.06,0:22:14.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかも エルサレムの神殿の再建の\N費用を出すと言うのです
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.78,0:22:20.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,歴代第二 36:22で\Nエズラはこう書いています
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.41,0:22:24.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,「エホバはキュロス王の心を\N奮い立たせ［た］」
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.00,0:22:28.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは自分が語った通りの\Nことが起きるよう
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.33,0:22:30.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,事態をコントロールできます
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.71,0:22:34.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのために 人の心さえ\N動かすことができます
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.76,0:22:39.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,たとえそれが キュロスのように\N異教の国の王であってもです
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.68,0:22:45.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,この布告により ユダヤ人は\Nユダに戻ることになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.23,0:22:51.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,建設プロジェクトをスタートさせ
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.73,0:22:55.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,都市全体を復興するのは\N大変な仕事です
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.65,0:23:00.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,祭壇の設置と神殿の再建を監督するよう
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.20,0:23:05.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,大祭司エシュアと\N総督ゼルバベルが任命されました
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.33,0:23:08.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,ところが問題にぶつかります
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.12,0:23:10.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,神殿の建設をやめさせようとして
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.63,0:23:13.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,反対者たちが妨害してきました
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.46,0:23:17.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初の妨害は失敗に終わりましたが
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.17,0:23:19.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,反対者たちの働き掛けにより
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.76,0:23:25.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,王はやがて神殿建設を禁止する\N命令を出します
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.35,0:23:27.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうなってしまうのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.93,0:23:31.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,約14年に及ぶ反対に意気をくじかれ
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.69,0:23:36.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,ユダヤ人たちはついに\N建設をやめてしまいました
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.07,0:23:40.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,神殿建設には\N重要なことが関わっていました
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.74,0:23:42.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル書の預言によれば
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.74,0:23:49.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムと神殿はメシアが現れる前に\N建て直されることになっていました
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.16,0:23:53.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 建設は中止され\N神殿は未完成のままです
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.50,0:23:56.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,このままだとメシアは現れません
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.42,0:23:59.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,エシュアとゼルバベルは\N助けを必要としていました
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.84,0:24:03.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,事を導くため エホバが行動します
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.14,0:24:07.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,まず 預言者ハガイを遣わします
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.43,0:24:12.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハガイはユダヤ人たちに\N問題点をはっきり指摘します
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.85,0:24:16.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,反対があっても\N神殿の建設を続けるように と
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.02,0:24:18.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの指示を伝えます
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.03,0:24:22.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,ユダヤ人たちはどうするでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.03,0:24:26.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,反対に屈し 建設を諦めるでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.12,0:24:30.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,それとも エホバの言葉に従って\N建設を続けるでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.96,0:24:35.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,事を導くため エホバはさらに\N預言者ゼカリヤを遣わすことにし
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.88,0:24:39.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,大切なメッセージが込められた\N幻を見せます
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.38,0:24:43.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,ゼカリヤは エホバが\N反対者たちの妨害から守ってくれて
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.51,0:24:46.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,神殿を再建できるように\Nしてくれることを伝えました
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.01,0:24:51.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,神殿を再建できるよう\Nエホバが導いてくれます
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.14,0:24:55.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが遣わした2人の預言者の言葉に\N勇気づけられ 
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.15,0:24:58.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,ユダヤ人たちは神殿の建設を\N再開しました
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.94,0:25:02.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして紀元前515年に完成させました
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.03,0:25:09.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも その時のユダヤ人の熱意は\Nやがて失われ 数十年が経過します
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.46,0:25:16.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,神殿は完成しましたが エルサレムの\N城壁や門は所々が崩れたままで
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.96,0:25:19.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,修復されていませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.17,0:25:24.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは重大なことでした 周りの国に\Nいつ攻められてもおかしくありません
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.13,0:25:29.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,城壁がないと エルサレムは\N無防備のままになってしまいます
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.43,0:25:33.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤはそのことを聞いて\Nひどく悲しみます
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.40,0:25:36.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムはどう？
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.81,0:25:38.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんな元気？
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.73,0:25:41.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,いやぁ～
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.78,0:25:45.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても大変なことになっています
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.57,0:25:49.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムの城壁は破壊されたままで
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.08,0:25:51.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,門も焼かれたままなんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.91,0:25:54.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,神殿は？
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.54,0:25:59.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,あるよ でもきちんとした奉仕は\N行われていない
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.04,0:26:03.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,祭司たちでさえ神の律法を守ってない
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.92,0:26:08.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムの状況を聞いて\Nネヘミヤは大きなショックを受けました
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.43,0:26:12.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,その頃 彼はシュシャンで\Nペルシャの王の献酌人をしていました
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.81,0:26:16.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,シュシャンとエルサレムは\N1600キロほど離れています
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.69,0:26:21.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでも ネヘミヤは\N何とかしなければと考えます
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.99,0:26:33.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤは 城壁を修復できることを\N知って 喜びました
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.25,0:26:40.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,ユダヤ人たちはやはり\N反対者たちを恐れていましたが 
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.59,0:26:43.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤは勇気づけようとしました
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.30,0:26:48.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤは これはエホバが\N望んでいることだと知っていました
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.64,0:26:50.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが望んでいるのであれば
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.89,0:26:55.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰がどんなに反対しようとも\N妨げることはできません
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.77,0:26:59.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,城壁の修復は始まります
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.44,0:27:06.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,もちろん 何の問題もなく\Nうまくいくわけではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.95,0:27:10.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,反対者たちは諦めていません
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.07,0:27:12.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,いい考えがあります
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.24,0:27:16.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤを反逆の罪で\N訴えるのはどうでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.58,0:27:18.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,それはいい
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.92,0:27:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,なるほど その手があるな
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.04,0:27:24.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤを追い込んでやる
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.46,0:27:29.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,反対者たちはユダヤ人たちをののしり\N策略を巡らし
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.18,0:27:34.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,王に反逆しているとネヘミヤに\N言い掛かりをつけることまでします
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.81,0:27:41.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤと城壁を修復する\Nユダヤ人たちは窮地に立たされます
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.69,0:27:46.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでも彼らは\Nエホバが導いてくれることを確信して
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.53,0:27:49.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,修復工事を続けました
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.70,0:27:54.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバがこうなると一度宣言したなら
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.95,0:27:59.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,その通りになるのを阻むことは\N誰にもできません
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.50,0:28:03.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムの再建と城壁の完成は
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.29,0:28:05.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが望んでいることなので
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.92,0:28:08.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤはエホバが修復工事を
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.76,0:28:13.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,必ずサポートしてくれると\N確信することができました
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.10,0:28:15.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして そのサポートにより
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.26,0:28:20.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムの城壁は\Nわずか52日で完成しました
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.77,0:28:25.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤ ついに完成だ！
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.44,0:28:30.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,よくやったな！
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.66,0:28:34.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,神殿も城壁も完成し
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.78,0:28:38.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムの環境は整いました
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.45,0:28:40.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 約12年後
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.00,0:28:44.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤはシュシャンに\N戻ることになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.50,0:28:48.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤがいない間\Nユダヤ人は正しい崇拝を
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.13,0:28:50.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,だんだん行わなくなっていきました
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.97,0:28:55.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,また悪い行いをするように\Nなってしまいました
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.60,0:29:01.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,大祭司エルヤシブなどの祭司たちも\N不正を行うようになっていました
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.31,0:29:04.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで エホバは\N堕落した祭司たちを正すために
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.90,0:29:08.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,預言者マラキを遣わします
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.65,0:29:11.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜレビ族はエホバの名を\N軽んじているんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.36,0:29:12.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,軽んじている？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.57,0:29:16.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなた方は\N欠陥のある動物を捧げながら
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.28,0:29:18.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,悪いことではないと言っている
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.62,0:29:21.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは受け入れられるだろうか？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.04,0:29:25.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,それに 神が犠牲を受け入れられない\Nほかの理由もあります
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.88,0:29:30.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなた方は若い時からの妻を\N裏切っています
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.63,0:29:34.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,祭司の唇は知識を保つべきであり
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.80,0:29:37.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,民は祭司の口に律法を求めるべきです
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.76,0:29:42.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,なのに あなた方は\N多くの人の信仰を妨げています
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.69,0:29:49.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,残念なことに マラキの訴えは\N祭司たちに響かなかったようです
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.53,0:29:53.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんなに忠告しても\N全く変わろうとしませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.57,0:29:59.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムに戻ったネヘミヤは\Nひどい状況を見てがくぜんとします
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.62,0:30:04.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,長いこと祭司とレビ族は\N務めを果たしていません
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.12,0:30:08.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,それを見て人々は\N10分の1を納めなくなりました
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.09,0:30:11.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで祭司たちは\N畑仕事に戻ってしまいました
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.84,0:30:15.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルヤシブは食料を持ってくるよう\N人々に言わなかったのですか
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.51,0:30:17.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたが留守の間 マラキが
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.60,0:30:21.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルヤシブと祭司たちに\N警告を与えました
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.23,0:30:26.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも エルヤシブは\N食料の置かれていたこの部屋を
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.77,0:30:30.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,食堂としてトビヤに使わせています
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.53,0:30:35.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,人々は10分の1を納めないだけでなく
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.28,0:30:39.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,安息日に商売を始めることさえします
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.33,0:30:42.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,今日は何があるの？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.41,0:30:45.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,おいしい魚だ ティルスのね
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.92,0:30:48.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,外国人と結婚してもいました
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.29,0:30:50.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,今日 ギズラと結婚する
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.30,0:30:52.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,ギズラ？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.55,0:30:54.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,モアブ人の？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.97,0:31:00.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほかの民族の女性と\N結婚しないって誓ったよね？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.35,0:31:05.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,このままだとメシアに至る家系に\N影響が及び
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.31,0:31:08.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,異教の崇拝が入り込んでくる\N恐れがあります
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.31,0:31:10.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,せっかく復興したのに
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.32,0:31:14.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,またエホバに見放されても\Nおかしくないことをしていたのです
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.49,0:31:17.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムがバビロンに\N滅ぼされることになった時と
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.66,0:31:20.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,同じ間違いをしていました
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.58,0:31:25.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでネヘミヤは\N事態を正すために立ち上がります
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.46,0:31:33.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんなでこの部屋を清め\N全て元に戻しなさい
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.17,0:31:33.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,やめてくれ
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.92,0:31:34.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,おっしゃる通りに
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.72,0:31:38.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,全てのレビ族と歌い手たち\N代官たちを集めなさい
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.18,0:31:40.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんなを持ち場に戻らせます
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.22,0:31:43.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,安息日をしっかり守るようにと言います
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.14,0:31:47.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,一体どういうつもりだ？\N昨日は野宿したんだぞ
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.60,0:31:52.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,律法を知ってますよね\N安息日には仕事も商売もしてはいけない
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.78,0:31:57.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,帰りなさい！安息日を神聖なものと\Nするために見張ってください
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.95,0:32:00.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰も入れてはいけません
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.41,0:32:06.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,外国人と結婚している人たちも正します
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.25,0:32:10.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたは エホバに仕えていない人と\N結婚しないと誓いましたね
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.21,0:32:13.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネヘミヤ もう昔の話です
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.50,0:32:15.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,何言ってるんだ！
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.21,0:32:16.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,分かった 分かった！
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.67,0:32:21.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜ エホバの命令と\N自分の誓約を軽んじるのですか
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.39,0:32:26.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,間違いなく エホバが\Nネヘミヤをずっと導いていました
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.27,0:32:29.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,この大々的な立て直しにより
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.98,0:32:33.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,再び平和が戻ってきました
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.82,0:32:37.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,背教者たちが一掃された\Nこの記録をもって
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.86,0:32:41.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヘブライ語聖書の最終章は\N終わっています
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.83,0:32:50.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこからイエスの誕生までの\N数百年の記録は 聖書に載っていません
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.42,0:32:55.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 歴史によると エルサレムには\Nその間 いろいろな変化がありました
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.01,0:32:58.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,メディア･ペルシャは\Nギリシャに征服されます
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.84,0:33:04.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネブカドネザルが見た像の\N銅の腹とももに相当する国です
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.26,0:33:08.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,ギリシャが治めるようになっても\Nエルサレムは無事に存続しましたが
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.98,0:33:12.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,崇拝の面ではそうはいきませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.52,0:33:14.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,ギリシャ帝国の繁栄により
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.73,0:33:19.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,ギリシャの言語 文化\N宗教思想が広まっていき
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.65,0:33:22.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,イスラエルもその影響を受けました
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.95,0:33:25.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,後に アンティオコス4世は
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.79,0:33:29.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,ユダヤ人の宗教と習慣を\N根絶しようとしました
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.96,0:33:33.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの神殿でギリシャの神ゼウスに
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.50,0:33:37.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,豚を犠牲として捧げることまでしました
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.63,0:33:41.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは正しい崇拝を汚す\Nひどい行為でした
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.68,0:33:45.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,ところが これにより\N思わぬ展開になります
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.43,0:33:48.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,決起したユダヤ人たちが反乱を起こし
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.56,0:33:53.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,神殿を清めて\N再びエホバに奉献しました
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.73,0:34:00.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,約100年後 ギリシャに代わって\N別の大国ローマが登場し
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.36,0:34:03.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムもその統治下に入ります
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.49,0:34:09.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネブカドネザルが見た像の\N鉄のすねに相当する国です
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.87,0:34:14.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヘロデ大王の統治の下\Nエルサレムは非常に繁栄しました
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.83,0:34:17.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヘロデ大王の一番の功績は
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.42,0:34:20.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,神殿とそれに付属する建物の再建です
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.01,0:34:26.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,神殿で犠牲を捧げることは イエスが\N生まれる頃にも行われていました
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.30,0:34:30.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の記録はその頃から再び始まります
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.95,0:34:47.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバ 憐れみを！
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.20,0:34:47.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,何ごとだ？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.78,0:34:49.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,もう朝なの？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.58,0:34:52.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,あれは天使かな？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.87,0:34:54.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,恐れることはありません
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.87,0:35:00.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,見よ 私は大きな喜びとなる\N良い知らせを告げているのです
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.51,0:35:05.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,今日 ダビデの都市で\N主なるキリストが生まれたからです
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.22,0:35:10.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスについての多くの預言が\Nその通りになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.02,0:35:15.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,西暦29年 エホバは\Nイエスに聖なる力を注ぎます
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.94,0:35:18.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,これはまさに500年以上も前に
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.98,0:35:23.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバがダニエルに伝えた\N預言の通りの事でした
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.19,0:35:26.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,約束されていたメシアが現れました
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.99,0:35:32.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,宣教を始めた頃\Nイエスはイザヤの預言を読み上げます
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.54,0:35:37.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,イザヤにはこうあります
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.63,0:35:41.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,「エホバの聖なる力が私の上にある
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.67,0:35:43.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,神が私を選び
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.92,0:35:47.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,貧しい人に良い知らせを\N告げるようにさせたからである
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.72,0:35:51.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,私は神から遣わされて\N捕らわれている人に釈放を
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.97,0:35:55.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,目が見えない人に視力の回復を知らせ
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.39,0:35:58.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに受け入れられる年を伝える」
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.86,0:36:10.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,今日 皆さんが聞いたこの聖句が
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.33,0:36:12.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,実現しています
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.96,0:36:25.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖なる力を受けて イエスはわずか\N数年の間にたくさんの奇跡を行いました
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.76,0:36:29.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,多くの人がイエスを\N信じるようになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.34,0:36:32.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,私 実は病気で
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.60,0:36:38.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,12年ほど血の流出に\N苦しんでいるんです
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.06,0:36:40.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスなら治せます！
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.19,0:36:45.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,あの方の外衣の房べりに\N触れることができれば
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.65,0:36:48.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,良くなるでしょう！
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.33,0:37:00.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰か触りましたか？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.58,0:37:02.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,私の外衣に
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.00,0:37:06.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,主よ どうか お許しください
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.67,0:37:09.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,触ったのは私です！
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.97,0:37:13.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰を持ったのです！
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.18,0:37:15.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたに
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.27,0:37:21.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,その外衣の房べりに触れるだけで\N私は良くなる と思いました
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.81,0:37:24.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,娘よ！
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.86,0:37:28.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの信仰が良くならせました
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.91,0:37:35.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,これまで見たこともないような\N奇跡を見て 人々は驚きました
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.04,0:37:38.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,ついに 希望を見つけました
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.83,0:37:42.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,明るい将来がある という希望です
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.33,0:37:46.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかも 世界を良くしようとする\Nどんな人にもできないことを
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.34,0:37:48.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスは行いました
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.34,0:37:51.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,連れてきました
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.14,0:38:02.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,主よ もしいてくださったなら
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.69,0:38:05.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼は死ななかったでしょう！
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.82,0:38:17.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,ラザロよ 出てきなさい！
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.14,0:38:38.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,さあ 解いてあげなさい！
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.22,0:38:44.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスが行ったことは私たちに\N素晴らしいことを教えてくれます
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.15,0:38:46.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバがどんな世界を願い
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.52,0:38:48.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,どれほどの力を持っているか
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.03,0:38:52.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスが治める世界での暮らしが
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.11,0:38:55.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,どれほど平和で幸せなものか
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.49,0:38:59.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスの力を見た人たちは\N大きな期待を抱きました
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.75,0:39:02.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスはわずか3年半の間に
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.46,0:39:05.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,非常に多くのことを行いました
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.29,0:39:09.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,メシアについて預言されていたことが\N次々と起き
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.25,0:39:13.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスは杭に掛けられて\N処刑されました
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.69,0:39:28.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスが命を\N犠牲として捧げたことにより
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.90,0:39:33.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバへの崇拝の仕方が\N大きく変わりました
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.45,0:39:36.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,動物の犠牲はもう必要ありません
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.37,0:39:41.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,崇拝のためにエルサレムの神殿に\N行く必要も もうありません
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.16,0:39:45.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,メシアを通して行うのが\Nエホバへの正しい崇拝です
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.96,0:39:48.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスの犠牲に信仰を持つなら
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.54,0:39:54.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに喜ばれ 誰もが明るい将来を\N見つめることができます
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.30,0:39:58.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,モーセの律法に基づく\N崇拝の取り決めは終わりました
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.51,0:40:01.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムも神殿ももう必要ありません
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.89,0:40:05.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつまでも平和に暮らせる世界を\N可能にするのは
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.31,0:40:07.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスが捧げた犠牲です
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.61,0:40:12.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでは エルサレムと神殿は\Nどうなるのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.69,0:40:14.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスは亡くなる前
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.74,0:40:19.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムが陥落することについて\N知らせ 指示を与えました
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.49,0:40:23.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,ルカ 21:20, 21で\Nこう言っています
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.20,0:40:27.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,「エルサレムが陣営を張った軍隊に\N囲まれるのを見たなら 
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.33,0:40:31.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,その時 荒廃が近づいたことを\N知りなさい⋯⋯
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.05,0:40:33.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,都の中にいる人はそこを出なさい
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.84,0:40:37.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,田舎にいる人は\N都に入ってはなりません」
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.13,0:40:40.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスは素晴らしい指導者です
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.05,0:40:43.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の王国の王になるのは\Nまだ先のことでしたが
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.35,0:40:46.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,王として優れた素質を持っていることが
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.23,0:40:50.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,この時のイエスの行動から\Nよく分かります
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.48,0:40:55.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムとユダヤから逃げるようにと\N指示することによって
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.32,0:41:00.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスは1世紀のクリスチャンたちを\N導き 守りました
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.49,0:41:02.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスは都市の陥落を預言し
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.95,0:41:07.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,数十年後 預言はその通りになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.79,0:41:12.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,西暦66年 ユダヤは依然として\Nローマ帝国の配下にあり
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.00,0:41:18.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのことに不満を募らせたユダヤ人が\Nついに反乱を起こします
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.36,0:41:34.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,やって来たローマ軍に\Nエルサレムは完全に包囲され
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.15,0:41:36.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,逃げようがないと思われました
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.74,0:41:40.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも エホバの言葉は\N必ずその通りになります
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.87,0:41:44.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスが言ったように\N逃げるタイミングがやって来ました
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.62,0:41:48.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,どういうわけか\Nローマ軍が撤退したのです
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.12,0:41:53.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,その機会を逃さずに イエスに\N言われていた通りにした人たちは
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.92,0:41:57.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,安全な所へ逃げることができました
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.51,0:42:06.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,反対に すぐに行動しなかった人たちは\N逃げられなくなりました
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.27,0:42:19.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,もはや エルサレムはエホバにとって\N特別な都市ではありませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.65,0:42:22.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,守られることはありません
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.45,0:42:30.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,都市と神殿は完全に破壊されました
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.84,0:42:42.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,1世紀のクリスチャンが
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.84,0:42:47.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスから前もって\N警告を与えられていたのと同じように
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.10,0:42:50.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちも警告を与えられています
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.06,0:42:54.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界の体制の終わりが近づいた時に\Nどんなことが起きるかを
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.56,0:42:58.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスはあらかじめ教えてくれました
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.11,0:43:00.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の預言によれば
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.11,0:43:03.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,今が終わりの時代であることは\N間違いありません
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.66,0:43:08.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは 今後どうなるかについて\N細かなことまでは言っていません
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.12,0:43:12.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも エホバが言ったことは\N全て必ずその通りになります
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.58,0:43:17.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは私たちに 人類が\N平和になる前の終わりの時代に
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.42,0:43:21.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界情勢がどのように変化していくかを\N教えてくれています
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.55,0:43:24.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,考えてみてください\Nダニエル書の預言によれば
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.89,0:43:31.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,今の体制が終わる頃 1つの政治勢力が\N世界で大きな力を持っているはずです
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.56,0:43:33.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,第1次世界大戦の頃
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.69,0:43:37.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,鉄と粘土の足に相当する\N政治勢力が現れました
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.94,0:43:41.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,大戦中 イギリスとアメリカは\N協力関係を結び
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.78,0:43:45.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,第2次世界大戦の時もそうでした
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.52,0:44:18.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,英語を話す緊密なこの2つの国は
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.48,0:44:21.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界で大きな力を持ってきました
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.61,0:44:27.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,この政治勢力が鉄と粘土で\N表されているのは適切なことです
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.70,0:44:32.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,足の指には鉄の部分と\N粘土の部分があるので
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.79,0:44:39.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,この王国には強い部分と\Nもろい部分があることになります
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.17,0:44:44.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,アメリカとイギリスは戦争に関わり
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.84,0:44:48.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,鉄のような強さを見せてきました
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.89,0:44:53.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 粘土が混ざっているので
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.93,0:44:56.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,もろさがあります
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.90,0:44:59.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,反対意見を持つ一般市民がいるために
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.61,0:45:03.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,鉄のような強さを\N発揮できないことがあります
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.49,0:45:06.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の預言通り
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.49,0:45:10.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界情勢や社会の動向が\N刻々と変化しても
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.45,0:45:12.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは安心していられます
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.00,0:45:15.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが私たちを導いてくれます
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.96,0:45:20.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,世の中がますますおかしくなり\N悪くなっていってもです
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.09,0:45:24.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,何も変わっていない\N何も問題はない と思って
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.97,0:45:28.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,生活を続けていた\N1世紀の人たちと同じように
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.34,0:45:32.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,現代の人も今の生活をただ続けています
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.43,0:45:34.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 私たちは注意を怠りません
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.85,0:45:39.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,今 世界で起きていることが\N預言の通りであることを忘れません
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.52,0:45:43.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,この王たちの時代に
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.61,0:45:48.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,天の神は決して滅ぼされることのない\N王国を建てます
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.49,0:45:53.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,啓示の書から\Nこの先 何が起こるかが分かります
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.87,0:46:00.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界の国々が これまで以上に\N国際連合に力を委ねるようになります
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.25,0:46:03.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 使徒パウロが言っているように
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.17,0:46:06.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,国々は「平和だ！安全だ！」と\N宣言します
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.97,0:46:10.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも それは本当の平和ではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.34,0:46:12.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,国連を支持する国々が
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.60,0:46:17.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,神を正しく崇拝していない宗教を\N攻撃します
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.65,0:46:29.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,それから エゼキエルが「マゴグの地の\Nゴグ」と呼んでいる諸国家の連合体が
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.45,0:46:33.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを崇拝する人たちを攻撃します
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.08,0:46:36.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 恐れる必要はありません
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.41,0:46:40.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,その時こそ これまで学んできたことを\N生かす時です
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.50,0:46:43.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが導いてくれると信じる人たちは
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.50,0:46:46.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,恐れることなく\N将来を見つめることができます
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.67,0:46:49.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,これまで見てきたように\Nエホバはいつでも
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.34,0:46:51.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,思った通りに事を進めてきました
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.68,0:46:53.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,ただ指示を与えるだけで
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.68,0:46:57.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,何のサポートもしないということは\N決してありませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.14,0:47:01.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで 私たちがこれまで\N学んできた人たちについての記録は
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.52,0:47:04.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,ただの感動的な話ではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.11,0:47:09.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはずっと人類を平和にするために\N事を進めてきたのです
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.15,0:47:14.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,振り返ってみると エホバは\N大切な人たちをいつでも導いてきました
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.37,0:47:18.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,これまでずっと いつも\Nエホバが思った通りになってきました
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.54,0:47:22.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,この先はそうならない ということが\Nあり得るでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.04,0:47:24.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが初めに決めたことが
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.25,0:47:28.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,その通りになるのを阻むことは\N誰であろうと決してできません
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.92,0:47:31.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはただ見てきただけ\Nではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.51,0:47:34.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,昔も今も事を導いています
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.64,0:47:36.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,考えてみてください
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.64,0:47:41.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,これまでエホバが大切な人たちを\N導いてきたのであれば
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.14,0:47:44.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,たとえ もうどうにもならないと\N思えるようなときでも
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.65,0:47:48.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを信頼し\Nエホバの言われる通りにすれば
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.82,0:47:53.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,必ず助けてくれると\N確信できるのではないのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.24,0:47:56.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに不可能なことはありません
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.12,0:47:59.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんなことがあっても
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.12,0:48:01.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,必ず助けてくれます
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.63,0:48:07.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,戦う必要はありません
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.30,0:48:16.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,恐れなくてよいのです
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.64,0:48:21.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,全てエホバが考えた通りになります
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.65,0:48:28.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,その王国はほかのどんな民にも\N渡されません
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.03,0:48:34.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,これらの王国を全て打ち砕いて終わらせ
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.05,0:48:54.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,その王国だけが永遠に存続します
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.51,0:48:57.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の王国が世界を治め
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.05,0:49:00.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,地球全体が楽園になります
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.89,0:49:06.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの約束が\N完全にその通りになります
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.98,0:49:13.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちがずっと願ってきた人類の平和が\Nついに実現し もう失われません
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.90,0:49:15.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスの統治によって
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.99,0:49:20.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界がどんなふうに新しくなるか\N想像してみてください
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.29,0:49:25.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,これまで誰も見たことがないような\N素晴らしい世界になります
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.50,0:49:29.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこにいる時のことを\N思い描いてみてください
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.77,0:49:55.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私は新しい天と新しい地を\N創造している
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.49,0:50:00.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,以前の事柄は思い出されることも
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.28,0:50:03.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,心に浮かぶこともない」
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.67,0:50:11.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,「正しい人は地上に住み続け
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.25,0:50:14.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこで永遠に暮らす」
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.32,0:50:39.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,「神は死を永久にのみ込む
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.07,0:50:46.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,主権者である主エホバは\N全ての顔から涙を拭う」
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.13,0:50:58.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,「神は人々の目から\N全ての涙を拭い去ります
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.30,0:51:01.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,もはや死はなくなり
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.76,0:51:08.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,悲しみも嘆きも苦痛もなくなります
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.23,0:51:11.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,以前のものは過ぎ去ったのです」
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.46,0:51:42.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,「その時 目が見えない人は\N見えるようになり
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.68,0:51:47.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,耳が聞こえない人は聞こえるようになる
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.40,0:51:58.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,その時 足が不自由な人は\N鹿のように跳びはね
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.90,0:52:04.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,口が利けない人は歓声を上げる
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.62,0:52:11.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,荒野に水が湧き出て
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.75,0:52:19.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,砂漠平原に川が流れる」
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.72,0:52:28.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,「人々は家を建てて住み
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.94,0:52:41.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,ブドウ園を造って実を食べる」
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.66,0:52:56.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私の民の寿命は木の寿命のようになり
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.84,0:53:00.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,私が選んだ者たちは
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.51,0:53:04.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,働く喜びを存分に味わう」
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.39,0:53:10.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,「温厚な人は地上に住み続け
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.90,0:53:18.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,豊かな平和をこの上なく喜ぶ」
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.75,0:53:37.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,信仰が強まりました
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.42,0:53:42.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,全てエホバが考えた通りに\Nなるので安心です
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.09,0:53:47.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,うれしいことに ドラマ「エホバは\N平和へと導いてくださる」
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.64,0:53:54.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,第1部と第2部は jw.orgと\NJW Library®アプリで
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.56,0:53:59.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,早速ダウンロードすることができます
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.48,0:54:06.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんはこれまで 大会の\Nオリジナルソングを楽しんできましたか
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.53,0:54:12.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,これから 過去数年の地区大会で歌った\Nオリジナルソングを聞きながら
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.29,0:54:15.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,大会で学んだことを\N思い返してみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.67,0:54:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,お楽しみください
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.56,0:54:44.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,立ちはだかる恐れの壁
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.44,0:54:54.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,神が共にいて道を拓く
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.04,0:55:04.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,敵の軍が押し寄せても
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.67,0:55:14.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしの命は神が守る
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.77,0:55:24.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバ すぐそばにいてください
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.82,0:55:35.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,敵より強い軍 見えるように
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.54,0:55:44.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,今ください 耐えるために
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.05,0:55:56.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,勇気ください 勝利近い
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.35,0:56:07.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,不意に襲う不安の波
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.78,0:56:17.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の力の弱さを知る
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.50,0:56:27.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,神に勇気求めるなら
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.96,0:56:37.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,だれもその勇気取り去れない
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.02,0:56:48.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバ すぐそばにいてください
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.15,0:56:58.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,敵より強い軍 見えるように
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.83,0:57:08.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,今ください 耐えるために
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.26,0:57:23.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,勇気ください 勝利近い
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.78,0:57:38.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,見渡せば あふれる愛
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.70,0:57:44.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,大切な仲間
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.58,0:57:52.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,あとにした今の世では
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.38,0:57:58.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,見られない景色
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.43,0:58:12.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,試みを越え 愛は残る
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.69,0:58:26.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,さあ 進もう 神と歩む愛の道を
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.58,0:58:36.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,今日 確かに 心にある
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.47,0:58:48.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちの愛は決して
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.86,0:59:02.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,さあ 進もう 神と歩む愛の道を
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.54,0:59:12.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,今日 確かに 心にある
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.50,0:59:27.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちの愛は決して絶えない
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.48,0:59:43.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,この愛 絶えない
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.66,0:59:58.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,炎のように迫る敵たち
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.39,1:00:03.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,恐れはしない
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.43,1:00:12.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつもそばにエホバがいるから
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.86,1:00:19.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの助けを信じ
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.66,1:00:26.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたから離れない
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.95,1:00:34.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,力もらって強くなろう
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.59,1:00:40.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,進みつづけていこう
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.26,1:00:44.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたと
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.19,1:01:07.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,未来が見える もう目の前に
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.50,1:01:14.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,守り抜く この信仰
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.00,1:01:21.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの勝利まで
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.43,1:01:28.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの助けを信じ
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.31,1:01:35.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたから離れない
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.48,1:01:43.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,力もらって強くなろう
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.11,1:01:49.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,進みつづけていこう
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.21,1:01:57.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,未来へ
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.18,1:02:14.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバと
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.24,1:02:28.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,星たちまたたく 夜の空
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.04,1:02:35.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,木陰に差し込む 陽の光
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.92,1:02:42.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバがその手ですべてを造った
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.72,1:02:47.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛込めて
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.64,1:03:03.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの創造 あなたの約束 心が躍る
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.28,1:03:10.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたからの愛 永遠にあふれ
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.20,1:03:22.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,この喜びに終わりはない
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.52,1:03:39.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,独り子が命を差し出し
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.36,1:03:49.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,永遠の歓喜を実現させた
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.62,1:04:03.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの創造 あなたの約束 心が躍る
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.38,1:04:10.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたからの愛 永遠にあふれ
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.22,1:04:22.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,この喜びに終わりはない
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.03,1:04:35.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,これから歌うのは 将来への確信を\N強める賛美の歌です
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.58,1:04:40.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,主題は 「新しい世界を見つめて」です
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.38,1:04:43.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,139番の歌を歌いましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.55,1:04:46.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,歌は139番です
